This paper deals with the verification of multiagent systems, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of Alternating-Time Temporal Logic (ATL) suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of pushdown systems and automata-based verification suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the focus on resource-constrained systems and multiagent systems suggests a connection to multiagent systems (cs.MA).
